<h2 style="text-align: center">Function 1: Student List</h2>

<p style="text-align: center"> &nbsp;&nbsp; You can see all the students who use this software as a student here which include all the information.</p>
<img src = "IntroductionImg/studentlist.png" alt="Students List" title="Students List" width="1000"/>
<p style="text-align: center">You can manage their accounts by using these buttons. 
<br/>The "add" button is for adding students to the lists. 
<br/>The "Edit" button is used to edit the information of the student.
<br/>And the "delete" button can remove the student from the list.</p>
<img src = "IntroductionImg/slist2.png" alt="Students List2" title="Students List2" width="1000"/>
<p style="text-align: center">Using these blanks to search for the student you want. Just adding his or her name or class, you can get it in the list.</p>
<img src = "IntroductionImg/slist3.png" alt="Students List3" title="Students List3" width="1000"/>

<p style="text-align: center"> &nbsp;&nbsp; You can all the students who use this software as a student here.
    <br/> &nbsp;&nbsp; You can also manage the information, include adding, searching and deleting.
</p>

<img src = "IntroductionImg/studentlist.png" alt="Students List" title="Students List" width="1000"/>

<HR align=center width=2000 color=#987cb9 SIZE=5>

<h2 style="text-align: center">Function 2: Teacher List</h2>
<p style="text-align: center">The Teacher List Function is just the same as Student List.
<br/>All the buttons and functions are all the same.</p>
<img src = "IntroductionImg/tlist.png" alt="Teacher List" title="Teacher List" width="1000"/>

<HR align=center width=2000 color=#987cb9 SIZE=5>

<h2 style="text-align: center">Function 3: Class List</h2>
<p style="text-align: center">Just like the Teacher List and Students List, Class List lists out all the classes that the students can choose.
<br/>As an administrator, you can add or delete a class if you want.
<br/>You can search for the class you want by using the searching box in case there are too many classes in the list.</p>
<img src = "IntroductionImg/clist.png" alt="Class List" title="Class List" width="1000"/>

